://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F171dbe8d-8882-4d70-8cdd-fc0aa9c7c946_1012x813.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F171dbe8d-8882-4d70-8cdd-fc0aa9c7c946_1012x813.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F171dbe8d-8882-4d70-8cdd-fc0aa9c7c946_1012x813.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F171dbe8d-8882-4d70-8cdd-fc0aa9c7c946_1012x813.jpeg" width="1012" height="813" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/171dbe8d-8882-4d70-8cdd-fc0aa9c7c946_1012x813.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:813,&quot;width&quot;:1012,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:110452,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F171dbe8d-8882-4d70-8cdd-fc0aa9c7c946_1012x813.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F171dbe8d-8882-4d70-8cdd-fc0aa9c7c946_1012x813.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F171dbe8d-8882-4d70-8cdd-fc0aa9c7c946_1012x813.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F171dbe8d-8882-4d70-8cdd-fc0aa9c7c946_1012x813.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NV.IND.MANF.ZS?end=2022&amp;locations=DE-US-JP&amp;start=1998">世界银行</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>这并不意味着这些国家的制造业不存在劳资冲突。例如，德国<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/features/2023-04-11/germany-s-economic-future-depends-on-its-non-fortune-500-companies?sref=R8NfLgwS">著名的“中小型”制造商</a>经常<a href="https://www.economist.com/business/2020/02/01/deutschland-ag-rethinks-workers-role-in-management">试图摆脱该国要求劳工在董事会中拥有代表权的要求</a>（一项称为“共同决定”的政策）。由于全球化的压力，<a href="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/iPOZFWTi_w38/v0/-1x-1.png">日本</a>和<a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/416156/trade-union-density-germany-y-on-y/">德国</a>的工会化程度随着时间的推移而下降。但是，尽管这些国家的集体谈判覆盖率较高，但相对于美国而言，这些国家在制造业方面取得的成功表明，工会与卓越制造业并非不相容。</p><p>这并不是我们应该关注的唯一这样的例子。一些人试图将美国基础设施成本高于其他发达国家的责任归咎于工会。但这些国家实际上比美国工会化程度更高，而且他们的工会<a href="https://www.economist.com/the-economist-explains/2014/03/17/why-french-trade-unions-are-so-strong">在政治上也更强大</a>。阿隆·利维（Alon Levy）对基础设施成本差异的研究可能比任何其他活着的人都更加仔细，他得出的结论是，<a href="https://pedestrianobservations.com/2019/01/08/meme-weeding-unions-and-construction-costs/">成本差异几乎没有归因于工会</a>。美国建筑工人的工资<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/view/articles/2017-05-31/the-u-s-has-forgotten-how-to-do-infrastructure?sref=R8NfLgwS">甚至比其他国家的工资高不了多少</a>。尽管某些地区的工会规则确实迫使交通机构雇用过多的员工，但利维得出的结论是，这只是一个次要因素。</p><p>换句话说，强大的工会与廉价的基础设施建设非常兼容——这正是我们美国脱碳所需要的。</p><h4>工会不应该消失，但其中一些需要改变做法</h4><p>换句话说，工会确实给产业政策带来了一些成本，但这不一定是严重或令人望而却步的成本。正如第二次世界大战的例子所表明的那样，协调劳工和实业家规划者的利益会带来政治好处。有迹象表明，这些政治利益在今天仍然是可以实现的——<a href="https://darrellowens.substack.com/p/yimby-triumph-in-california">见证许多工会转向加州因比阵营</a>是如何促成州立法机关现在通过的许多支持住房法案的。</p><p>因此，没有理由认为破坏工会应该成为我们产业政策的一部分，或者应该将工会从进步联盟中驱逐出去。与此同时，台湾建筑工人和抵制自动化港口的例子表明，美国工会有时确实会以挫败进步人士和实业家目标的方式行事。如果产业政策想要成功，他们就需要停止这样做。</p><p>因此，供应方进步人士需要想办法使工会和实业家的利益保持一致。这可能涉及在制定产业政策时给予劳工更多的参与权，以便工会明白新技术和外国工人不会对他们的生计构成威胁。这可能意味着德国共同决策的某种变体，或者只是将一些著名的工会领导人纳入实施 CHIPS 法案和 IRA 的规划过程中。这里的目标是让美国工会摆脱过去 40 年来一直处于的狂热防守状态，并让他们相信，他们以前视为威胁的事物——新技术和外国工人——现在代表着机遇。</p><p>与此同时，罗斯福研究所的人们需要停止<a href="https://twitter.com/toddntucker/status/1684588135919886337">表现得好像对工会行为的每一次批评</a>都是破坏工会和民主党联盟破裂的前奏。这种恐慌反应也是一种防御性的蹲伏，诞生于克林顿时代，当时民主党赢得选举的唯一途径就是向里根经济学做出让步。现在已经不是 1996 年了，现在已经是 1996 年了。进步人士现在正在制定经济政策议程。他们可以告诉工会“不，不要那样做，而是这样做”，而不会显得软弱和不团结。</p><p>最终，像大卫·达延和罗斯福研究所这样的人是正确的，进步的工业主义需要建立权力才能取得成功。但仅仅从联邦政府挪用资源的权力远不如为整个国家白手起家的权力。这是供应方进步派所理解的，值得他们赞扬。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/can-unions-and-industrial-policy?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/can-unions-and-industrial-policy?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p>; 
At least five interesting things for the middle of your week (#9)Room temperature superconductors, Chinese economic gloom, geoengineering, consumer confidence, and YIMBY victories https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least- Five-interesting-things-21a https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least- Five-interesting-things-21aNoah Smith Wed, 09 Aug 2023 08:12:25 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5cde9097-5aa9-4f24-bec9-63e335af2eb3_1400x700.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5cde9097-5aa9-4f24-bec9-63e335af2eb3_1400x700.jpeg" width="1400" height="700" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5cde9097-5aa9-4f24-bec9-63e335af2eb3_1400x700.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:700,&quot;width&quot;:1400,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:136555,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5cde9097-5aa9-4f24-bec9-63e335af2eb3_1400x700.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5cde9097-5aa9-4f24-bec9-63e335af2eb3_1400x700.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5cde9097-5aa9-4f24-bec9-63e335af2eb3_1400x700.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5cde9097-5aa9-4f24-bec9-63e335af2eb3_1400x700.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></figure></div><p>我在日本度过了一周回来了！通常当我去的时候，我会写一些关于日本的文章并与那里的一些人交谈，但这次我是带朋友到处走走，所以遗憾的是没有时间这样做。所以现在我对我不在的时候没有写下来的所有有趣的东西感到恼火，我正在努力追赶！</p><p>首先是我与 Eric Torenberg 合作的 Econ 102 播客的第五集。在这一期中，我们讨论高等教育的未来。这是 Spotify： </p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8a4dde160c6868a89c4742b15c&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;E5: Higher Ed, Being a Dorm Room Socrates, and the American Workforce&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith, Erik Torenberg&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/2AaG487XKjwnQLjMLMSZLt&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/2AaG487XKjwnQLjMLMSZLt" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p>这里有<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/e5-higher-ed-being-a-dorm-room-socrates-and/id1696419056?i=1000623772727">Apple</a> 、 <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QPlRE_6fG5Y">YouTube</a>和播客本身的<a href="https://link.chtbl.com/Econ102">订阅链接</a>。</p><p>无论如何，继续每周综述。</p><h4>对室温超导体感到兴奋是件好事</h4><p>LK99 的传奇似乎即将结束，一些研究人员声称这种材料是室温和环境压力超导体。正如<a href="https://twitter.com/MichaelSFuhrer/status/1686644227885944833">物理学家迈克尔·富勒（Michael Fuhrer）所解释的那样</a>，像这样的传奇故事很少以对最初主张的结论性反驳而结束。相反，随着复制尝试失败，它们会慢慢消失。通常，看似异常或奇怪的结果似乎会在所讨论的材料或方法周围突然出现，但它们很少是<em>相同的</em>奇怪结果，并且它们并不代表真正的突破会很快产生的那种结论性确认。</p><p>这似乎正是 LK99<a href="https://twitter.com/Andercot/status/1688598313497694208">所发生的情况</a>。<a href="https://eirifu.wordpress.com/2023/07/30/lk-99-superconductor-summary/#sbtable">复制尝试</a>要么全部失败，要么声称部分成功或出现无法解释的异常。现在，北京大学的一个研究小组<a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2308.03110.pdf">发表了一份非常仔细的复制尝试的预印本</a>，表明LK99不是超导体，只是铁磁体。某些材料的明显悬浮显然只是古老的铁磁性。这篇论文<a href="https://twitter.com/alexkaplan0/status/1688731316777275392">似乎让许多网上的炒作者相信</a>LK99 不是超导体。 （更新：<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2308.04353">另一篇论文没有发现</a>超导性，但确实发现了相变，可以解释其他团队在材料中发现的许多异常现象。）</p><p>与此同时，人们对复制的普遍乐观情绪已经崩溃： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg" width="964" height="492" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:492,&quot;width&quot;:964,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:114674,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4162d0de-ade3-4d5c-ac80-ec8f2160aa13_964x492.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://www.metaculus.com/questions/18177/room-temp-superconductor-replicated-by-2025/">Metaculus</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>室温环境压力超导体将是<a href="https://www.vox.com/future-perfect/23816753/superconductor-room-temperature-lk99-quantum-fusion">一件非常有用的东西</a>，但我们似乎还没有，而且我们似乎并不比几周前更接近获得一个。</p><p>这自然引出了下一个问题：这一切只是无用的炒作吗？嗯，不，我不这么认为，有两个原因。</p><p>首先，这一集向很多人介绍了科学过程的第一手资料。 1989 年，当两位化学家<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cold_fusion#:~:text=In%201989%2C%20a%20claim%20by,not%20replicate%20the%20excess%20heat.">声称实现了冷聚变</a>时，公众只是这一过程的旁观者；当复制失败时，大多数人要么只是在报纸上读到，要么就忘记了整个事情。但通过 LK99 的传奇故事，人们可以亲眼目睹科学家如何对待重大突破的说法。社交媒体为他们提供了重要的背景知识，迅速纠正神话和虚假信息，并让人们实时观察复制尝试。事实上，候选材料即使是业余爱好者也很容易在家制作，这使得一些普通人能够参与复制尝试。这种广泛的科学素养对我来说似乎是一件好事。</p><p>其次，LK99事件让人们对快速的技术进步感到兴奋。<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/techno-optimism-for-the-2020s">技术乐观主义</a>是这个博客的一大主题，很高兴看到人们对一块漂浮的岩石而不是对最新的文化战争粮食斗争感到兴奋。而且并不缺乏真正的科学突破来平衡虚假警报。<a href="https://www.statnews.com/2023/08/08/novo-nordisk-wegovy-cardiovascular-risk/">令人惊奇的有效抗肥胖药物</a>似乎是第一次被发明。 mRNA 疫苗突然在对抗从<a href="https://www.nih.gov/news-events/nih-research-matters/mrna-vaccine-treat-pancreatic-cancer">癌症</a>到<a href="https://www.reuters.com/business/healthcare-pharmaceuticals/biontech-initiates-clinical-trial-mrna-based-malaria-vaccine-candidate-2022-12-23/">疟疾</a>等各种疾病方面取得了巨大进展。最近在生成人工智能和廉价太空发射方面取得的进展令人惊叹。即使没有改变世界的飞跃，材料科学也一直在取得大量重大<a href="https://www.oodaloop.com/archive/2023/08/05/five-exciting-breakthroughs-in-materials-science/">进展</a>。</p><p>因此，希望 LK99 能够成为通向普遍技术乐观主义的入门药物。</p><h4>中国经济看起来持续疲软</h4><p>我已经写了不少有关中国经济放缓的文章，但负面消息却不断传来。随着<a href="https://twitter.com/jnordvig/status/1687787064874414080/photo/1">流入锐减和流出强劲</a>，中国的外国投资正在迅速减少： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg" width="900" height="552" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:552,&quot;width&quot;:900,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:49456,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7cdbf73d-2f69-4b07-b7c5-7b7c4e5d19d9_900x552.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://twitter.com/jnordvig/status/1687787064874414080/photo/1">Jens Nordvig</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>以美元计算，外国直接投资现已<a href="https://twitter.com/jnordvig/status/1687787066493460480">回到 20 世纪 90 年代的水平</a>，占 GDP 的比例将低得多。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/xi-china-economy-capital-investment-3439d31a">《华尔街日报》有一篇很好的报道</a>，讲述了中国地方政府如何四处恳求外国投资者投资，但很少有人接受。一些摘录：</p><blockquote><p>对于中国领导人来说，一方面对外国企业施加压力，另一方面又试图让它们投资，这正在成为一种越来越不稳定的平衡行为……</p><p>四川省省会成都的一位贸易官员最近开始了欧洲投资促进之旅。他空手而归……广东省南部一个县的一位高级官员……最近告诉一个来访的美国贸易团体，该县将奖励任何在该县投资的美国企业“决策者”，奖励其承诺交易价值的10%……贸易该组织拒绝了县官员的提议，这在美国将构成非法贿赂[。]</p></blockquote><p>为什么企业不投资中国？一句话，风险。最大的风险是战争风险，但正如《华尔街日报》详细介绍的那样，中国中央政府已经在以各种方式打击外国企业，企业技术被盗的风险也变得更加明显。重要的是要记住，<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/chinas-industrial-policy-has-mostly">中国在 20 世纪 90 年代和 2000 年代初成功的产业政策</a>几乎完全是<em>地方性的</em>，而不是国家性的；这是一群地方政府四处寻找外国投资者，并确保他们的投资得到回报。这已经不再起作用了，因为现在中央政府（即习近平）已经介入并开始扰乱这个公式。</p><p>外国直接投资大幅下降远不是中国唯一的坏消息。在经历了零疫情后的短暂冲击后， <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-08-08/china-s-trade-plunges-more-than-forecast-in-blow-to-recovery?sref=R8NfLgwS">出口现在正在下降</a>： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg" width="1200" height="675" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/cfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:675,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:122704,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfd5321b-973b-44e9-aaad-a9dcb881d19a_1200x675.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-08-08/china-s-trade-plunges-more-than-forecast-in-blow-to-recovery?sref=R8NfLgwS">彭博社</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>美国和日本等一些国家正在实现进口商品来源多元化。尽管美国经济蓬勃发展，但<a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2023/08/06/us-china-economy-trade-mexico/">仅在过去一年，美国从中国的进口就下降了 24%</a> 。墨西哥已取代中国成为美国最大贸易伙伴。 （当然，从附加值的角度来看，这种转变较小，因为其他国家向美国出口的一些产品中含有中国零部件。）</p><p>与此同时，中国地方政府<a href="https://twitter.com/RChoongWilkins/status/1688432888449318913">深陷困境</a>，无力偿还债务。这些政府中的大多数似乎都无力偿债，因为他们不提高财产税，因此只能通过出售土地来偿还债务，而这在房地产泡沫破灭期间效果不佳。他们可能需要接受救助，但即便如此，他们未来的自筹资金能力也受到影响。</p><p>习近平政府如何应对这一连串坏消息？ <a href="https://www.semafor.com/article/08/07/2023/china-restricts-economists-from-discussing-risks">正如你所期望的，</a>一个不安全的独裁者会做出这样的反应：</p><blockquote><p>尽管所有迹象都表明未来形势严峻，但北京仍限制当地经济学家讨论该国的经济困境。</p><p>大学和智囊团的研究人员以及券商分析师告诉英国《金融时报》，他们面临着压力，必须<a href="https://www.ft.com/content/b2e0ad77-3521-4da9-8120-1f0c1fdd98f8">积极报道经济新闻</a>，以增强公众信心。这与路透社早些时候的报道不谋而合，该报道详细介绍了中国公司如何被勒令不得在境外上市文件中<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/china/beijing-pushes-toning-down-china-risks-ipo-prospectuses-sources-2023-07-24/">讨论风险</a>，否则将面临失去首次公开募股批准的风险。</p></blockquote><p>与此同时，中国企业<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-08-08/bankers-forced-to-study-xi-s-thoughts-as-party-tightens-grip?utm_campaign=socialflow-organic&amp;utm_content=business&amp;cmpid=socialflow-twitter-business&amp;utm_source=twitter&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;sref=R8NfLgwS">被迫消耗</a>更多的“习近平思想”，每天长达几个小时。</p><p>每一天，<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/what-if-xi-jinping-just-isnt-that">我对习近平总体能力的评估</a>都会得到进一步的支持。</p><h4>好吧，也许地球工程有效</h4><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-21a">阅读更多</a></p>; 
