></figcaption></figure></div><p>如果说《美国的早晨》是乐观主义的高峰，那么 2023 年就是悲观主义的低谷，正如您从上面的图表中看到的那样。一项又一项的调查显示，美国人对当前经济的<a href="https://twitter.com/DKThomp/status/1687076787564449792">看法非常消极</a>。</p><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/if-this-is-a-bad-economy-please-tell">我一周前写了一篇文章，</a>试图思考为什么美国人可能对经济如此不安，因为失业率、工资和通货膨胀等指标在过去一年左右都出现了。其他人就同一主题<a href="https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2023/08/recession-doomers-economy/674900/">写了非常深思熟虑的文章</a>。但今天我想做一些稍微不同的事情——我想将 2023 年的拜登经济与 1984 年的里根经济进行比较。</p><h4>按照里根的标准，拜登的经济表现如何？</h4><p>当然，竞选连任的总统会选择强调最有利于他自己的记录的经济指标。因此，根据里根竞选团队认为他做对的事情来判断拜登的经济实际上是一个相当严格的标准。尽管如此，2023 年实际上在大多数方面都领先。</p><p>里根的广告宣扬了五件事：</p><ol><li><p>高就业率</p></li><li><p>较低的利率</p></li><li><p>较低的通货膨胀</p></li><li><p>大量购房</p></li><li><p>大量婚姻</p></li></ol><p>那么我们来做一下比较吧。 1984 年黄金年龄就业率约为 76%，而现在为 81%。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png" width="1318" height="450" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:450,&quot;width&quot;:1318,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:53031,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62ed5f02-c883-425e-ae81-602c60ecf42d_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>当时人口年轻化，退休人员较少，但即便如此， <a href="https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/EMRATIO">1984年的总就业率比现在还是略低</a>。</p><p>现在，我认为重要的是不仅要看这些经济指标的<em>水平</em>，还要看<em>最近的变化</em>，因为人们的参照点很重要。在 1984 年和 2023 年，高就业率都是一个相对较新的事物；在美国，我们刚刚从新冠疫情中恢复过来，大衰退仍在人们的记忆中，而 1984 年，美国正从 20 世纪 70 年代的滞胀和保罗·沃尔克 (Paul Volcker) 为对抗通货膨胀而引发的衰退中恢复过来。</p><p>现在让我们看看利率。当里根大肆宣扬降低利率以帮助人们买房时，抵押贷款利率约为 13% 或略高。截至 2023 年，费率约为该数字的一半： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffeb53c90-4bf2-46d1-b452-a505ccff6ee8_958x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffeb53c90-4bf2-46d1-b452-a505ccff6ee8_958x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffeb53c90-4bf2-46d1-b452-a505ccff6ee8_958x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffeb53c90-4bf2-46d1-b452-a505ccff6ee8_958x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffeb53c90-4bf2-46d1-b452-a505ccff6ee8_958x450.png" width="958" height="450" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/feb53c90-4bf2-46d1-b452-a505ccff6ee8_958x450.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:450,&quot;width&quot;:958,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:51094,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:nu